description: Conjoined twins stand before a vendor selling kisses, one twin holding money. They are engaged in a tense argument about whose turn it is. The conflict is underscored by the surreal image of two heads sharing a body at a public stand. The absurdity peaks with one twin's bizarre threat to make "weird sucking sounds." This highlights the unique, dark humor arising from the mundane challenges of a conjoined existence.
caption: “It's my turn, Randy! Or I warn you ... I'll start making weird sucking sounds again!”
